- img_w and img_h are the native image dimensions you use to create keyframes
- ad_w and ad_h are animatediff dimensions, they're smaller to ensure everything fits in your VRAM
- fps is native frames you render your video at
- multiplier is the frame interpolation to use in the final processing step
- global seed will keep all your seeds consistent without manually changing each node

The animation works best at 3:2 aspect ratio.
